Parliament, Tuesday 18 June 2019 - Parliament is hosting the State of the Nation Address (SONA) by President Cyril Ramaphosa on 20 June 2019 at 19.00. Rehearsals for the Address will take place on Tuesday 18 June and Wednesday 19 June 2019 at Parliament.
	
	DETAILS FOR REHEARSALS ARE AS FOLLOWS: Members of the media who wish to cover the rehearsals must send their details (names, media house and ID number) to Nolizwi Magwagwa (nmagwagwa@parliament.gov.za, 021 403 2465 or 081 716 5824) and Masego Dlula (mdlula@parliament.gov.za , 021 403 8141, 081 715 9398) Due to SONA and associated preparations, a number of roads will be closed to normal traffic temporarily at various times between 18 to 20 June 2019. Affected streets and the applicable times have been advertised widely on radio and in the Western Cape daily newspapers to advise road users about the road closures. Copies of the affected roads can be obtained here
	https://tinyurl.com/y5cfw7dl or visit Parliament's website www.parliament.gov.za or Parliament's Facebook and Twitter pages at ParliamentofRSA. Parliament apologises for any inconvenience caused to members of the public by the temporary road closures. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICAÂ Enquiries: Moloto Mothapo 082 370 6930 A joint committee of Parliament monitors improvements in the quality of life and status of women in South Africa.Read more